gaffer.function.processor

Class Filter<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gaffer.function.processor.Processor<R,ConsumerFunctionContext<R,FilterFunction>>
      • gaffer.function.processor.Filter<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - The type of reference used by tuples.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ElementFilter

    public class Filter<R>
extends Processor<R,ConsumerFunctionContext<R,FilterFunction>>
    A Filter is a Processor that tests input Tuples against FilterFunctions. The functions are executed in order and the overall filter result for a given tuple is a logical AND of each filter function result. Tuples only pass the filter if all functions return a positive (true) result, and they fail as soon as any function returns a negative (false) result.

    If performance is a concern then simple, faster filters or those with a higher probability of failure should be configured to run first.
